gomodel:SYNGO_3798  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: CPEB2 activates GRASP1 mRNA Translation Contributing to AMPAR Recycling at synapse\n\nFurthermore in figure 5b immunohistochemistry on CPEB2 KO neurons shows less AMPAR at synapses. Experimental description: Forebrain-specific CPEB2 cKO mice, the male litter- mates from the mating of Cpeb2f/f,Camkii-Cre/+ females and Cpeb2f/f, +/+ male mice were used for behavior, electrophysiology, and biochemical studies." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" ;
